<br>
Hitsmode also allowed you to abbriviate the message about each hit from &quot;You punch a Drolvarg Gnarler for 20 damage&quot; to &quot;Punch 20&quot;...<br>
<br>
If you were used to it being in chat, then this is not a big thing, but if you are one that took advantage of it as soon as it was released, you missed it sorely after the new UI was released because it really did clean up the screen and chat window...<br>
<br>
The new way is almost as good, but not quite... it is much easier to set up now (i.e. - you can just click the settings vs. haveing to punch in a 30 character command line) but the end result is just not as clean as it was before... you would need to download a new skin that gets rid of all the &quot;frills&quot; of the new UI to make it closer to what it was before...<br>
<br>
So, how do you do it? <br>
1. Right click on your Chat window header bar... <br>
2. select window, <br>
3. select new window<br>
4. right click on new window header bar<br>
5. select rename window (make it &quot;My Hits&quot; or &quot;Me Hit&quot; - small title)<br>
6. right click new window header bar again<br>
7. select filter<br>
8. select melee<br>
9. select what type of hits you want in this window based on the title you just gave it (you will see a message in that window about the hits now being displayed there)<br>
10. right click the new window header bar<br>
11. select hitsmode<br>
12. select the type of hits you filtered to this window<br>
13. select the abbreviation type you want<br>
14. size and place the window accordingly...<br>
15. lock the window <p><a href="http://ebonmoon.com/index2.htm" target="_blank"><img src="http://ebonmoon.com/images/kel_bar.jpg" height=85 width=468 alt="Kelwin Jumala, GL - Shadows of the Ebon Moon on Vazaelle" border=0></a>
